.TH "open_mtd_device" 9 "open_mtd_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
open_mtd_device \- open MTD device by name, character device path, or number.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct mtd_info *" open_mtd_device
.BI "(const char *mtd_dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mtd_dev" 12
name, character device node path, or MTD device device number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function tries to open and MTD device described by \fImtd_dev\fP string,
which is first treated as ASCII MTD device number, and if it is not true, it
is treated as MTD device name, and if that is also not true, it is treated
as MTD character device node path. Returns MTD device description object in
case of success and a negative error code in case of failure.
